The paper proposes a novel Neural Architecture Search (NAS) approach for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) using the immune network theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on CNN architectures for image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new coding strategy and mutation strategy, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed approach on different datasets, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
